&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we are on a mission to help build a better Internet. Today the company runs one of the world’s largest networks that powers millions of websites and other Internet properties for customers ranging from individual bloggers to SMBs to Fortune 500 companies. Cloudflare protects and accelerates any Internet application online without adding hardware, installing software, or changing a line of code. Internet properties powered by Cloudflare all have web traffic routed through its intelligent global network, which gets smarter with every request. As a result, they see significant improvement in performance and a decrease in spam and other attacks. Cloudflare was named to Entrepreneur Magazine’s Top Company Cultures list and ranked among the World’s Most Innovative Companies by Fast Company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we’re not looking for people who wait for a polished roadmap; we’re looking for the builders who see the cracks in the Internet that everyone else has simply learned to live with. We value candidates who have the instinct to spot a &quot;normalized&quot; problem and the AI-native curiosity to create a solution using the latest tools. Our culture is built on iteration, leveraging AI to ship faster today to make it better tomorrow, while ensuring that every improvement, no matter how small, is shared across the team to lift everyone up. If you’re the type of person who values curiosity over bureaucracy, and that AI is a partner in solving tough problems to keep the Internet moving forward, you’ll fit right in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Available Locations: &lt;/strong&gt;Austin, San Francisco, New York&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an AI Automation Intern, you will be at the tactical center of integrating an acquired target company into Cloudflare. Your mission is to solve the &quot;fragmentation problem&quot; by centralizing tracking and updates from various workstreams—such as HR, Finance, and IT—into a unified view of progress. We are looking for an &lt;strong&gt;intellectually curious &quot;scrapper&quot;&lt;/strong&gt; who proactively looks for ways to solve problems with minimal guidance. Whether you build an agent from scratch or leverage existing AI tools like Gemini and NotebookLM, your goal is to make it easier for the M&amp;amp;A team to manage the overall integration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automate Executive Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and deploy workflows to automate the generation of executive-level reports on integration progress, ensuring leadership has proper visibility into the health of the deal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tactical Project Automation:&lt;/strong&gt; Build &quot;quick and dirty&quot; or structured solutions to automate the &quot;chasing&quot; of action items, gathering status updates, and reminding the deal team of past decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge Retrieval:&lt;/strong&gt; Use AI tools to organize and query past meeting notes and deal documents so the team can instantly recall critical commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Documentation:&lt;/strong&gt; Write clear technical requirement specifications and process maps that detail how these automated tracking and reporting workflows function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must-Have Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Currently enrolled &lt;/strong&gt;in an undergraduate degree in Economics, Finance, Business Administration or a related field.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available for a full-time 12-week internship, working from one of our US hub offices 3-5 days a week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Intellectual Curiosity:&lt;/strong&gt; A natural drive to explore new technologies and a &quot;figure it out&quot; mentality when faced with ambiguous tasks or minimal guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; Automation Fluency:&lt;/strong&gt; Practical experience using LLM interfaces (like Gemini or NotebookLM) or automation platforms to organize unstructured data and summarize complex information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical Writing:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong ability to draft technical documentation and translate messy project management hurdles into logical, automated workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Autonomous Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven ability to manage a project from an initial &quot;messy&quot; idea through to a functional, validated solution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Foundation:&lt;/strong&gt; Currently pursuing a degree in Computer Science, Data Science, or a related analytical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
